<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="argue-v">argue <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /'ɑːɡjuː/    美 /'ɑːrɡjuː/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>争论；争辩；争吵：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>argue (with sb) (about / over sth):</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Do you ever argue with your family about which TV programme to watch? 
你曾为看哪个电视节目和家人争论过吗？</p><footer>外研② – 6</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Gun control is a subject about which Americans have argued for a long time.
枪支管控是美国人争论已久的话题。</p><footer>2009 陕西</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>论证</strong></h4>
<p>to give reasons that support your opinion about sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The author <strong>argued for</strong> / <strong>against</strong> free university education.
作者给出理由主张/反对免费大学教育。</p><footer>2010 北京改</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It has been argued</strong> by some <strong>that</strong> gifted children should be grouped in special classes.
有些人论证说有天赋的孩子应该被分在专门的班级里。</p><footer>2011 广东</footer></div></div>